value.title: Biden says he feels 'a sense of history' living at White House
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Tuesday described the "sense of history" he feels residing at the White House and all the ways living in the historic building is an adjustment, including being waited on by White House staff.

value.title: White House to freeze out Mohammed bin Salman, Saudi prince who was close to Trump White House
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden is recalibrating U.S. diplomatic relations with Saudi Arabia, deploying a new approach that includes sidestepping Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman, who had a close relationship with the Trump administration.

value.title: Trump, ex-campaign manager Brad Parscale, meet at Mar-a-Lago: Source
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump met Tuesday with former campaign manager Brad Parscale at his Mar-a-Lago resort in Palm Beach, Florida, a source familiar with the matter told Fox News.

value.title: Trump calls McConnell a ‘political hack’ as GOP divide deepens post-impeachment
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump blistered Mitch McConnell as a “political hack," following McConnell’s speech calling Trump responsible Capitol riot.

value.title: Biden administration urges DHS officials to stop using ‘illegal alien’ in favor of ‘inclusive’ language
value.excerpt: The Biden administration is urging officials at the Department of Homeland Security to stop using phrases like “illegal alien” in favor of what it says are more “inclusive” terms -- part of a broader effort by the administration to change language use on immigration.

value.title: Plaskett insists Trump will 'never be elected again' despite impeachment acquittal
value.excerpt: Rep. Stacey Plaskett says Republicans made a calculation to save their political futures rather than convict Donald Trump.

value.title: Giuliani no longer representing Trump 'in any legal matters,' adviser says
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump's longtime personal attorney, Rudy Giuliani, is "not currently representing President Trump in any legal matters," senior Trump adviser Jason Miller told CNN on Tuesday.

value.title: Biden to press for Covid-19 relief package during CNN's Wisconsin town hall
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden, no longer encumbered by his predecessor's impeachment trial and eager to seize the national spotlight, will bring the case for his massive coronavirus relief plan to the country on Tuesday when he participates in a CNN town hall at 9 p.m. ET in Milwaukee.

value.title: Fauci defends Harris 'starting from scratch' claim, now knocks Trump vaccine rollout
value.excerpt: White House chief medical adviser Dr. Anthony Fauci reversed his previous rejection Tuesday of claims that the Biden administration was "starting from scratch" with the rollout of the coronavirus vaccine.

value.title: Biden, Cuomo didn’t discuss COVID nursing home scandal, Psaki says
value.excerpt: It was the elephant in the Oval Office, but somehow, President Biden and Gov. Andrew Cuomo didn’t discuss his COVID-19 nursing home scandal when they met last week.

value.title: Biden Early Approval Ratings Better Than Donald Trump, Barack Obama, George W Bush, Bill Clinton?
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden's approval ratings are trending positive early in his term, with 57% approving of his job performance in an early February poll and 62% doing so in a poll taken Sunday and Monday.

value.title: On Trump, Michigan Republicans Lean One Way: ‘Fealty at All Costs’
value.excerpt: Even after his defeat, Donald Trump is causing fierce infighting among Republicans in a crucial battleground state. Loyalists are rewarded. Dissenters face punishment.

value.title: Biden heads to Wisconsin, winter storms, Bill Gates book: 5 things you need to know Tuesday
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden travels to Wisconsin, another dose of severe weather is on the way and more news to start your Tuesday.

value.title: GOP Rep. Adam Kinzinger receives letter from 11 family members disowning him over Trump opposition
value.excerpt: Rep. Adam Kinzinger, a six-term Republican congressman representing Illinois, received a hand-written letter from 11 family members disowning him over his opposition of former President Donald Trump, Fox News has confirmed.

value.title: Federal judge blocks last-minute Trump rule limiting asylum claims
value.excerpt: A federal judge in California blocked a Trump-era rule that went into effect just a day before Joe Biden took office and sought to dramatically limit the ability of Central American migrants to claim asylum in the United States

value.title: Psaki: Gun control a 'priority,' Biden 'not afraid of standing up' to the NRA
value.excerpt: White House press secretary Jen Psaki on Tuesday said gun control is a "priority" for President Biden – and said he is "not afraid of standing up" to the National Rifle Association.

value.title: Rep. Bennie Thompson files civil lawsuit against Trump for Jan. 6 riot: 'We must hold him accountable'
value.excerpt: Rep. Bennie Thompson, D-Miss., on Tuesday filed a civil lawsuit against former President Trump, accusing him of inciting the deadly Jan. 6 Capitol riot and conspiring with attorney Rudy Giuliani and extremist groups to stop Congress from certifying President Biden's Electoral College win.

value.title: NAACP and Democratic congressman sue Trump, Giuliani over Capitol assault
value.excerpt: The lawsuit accuses Trump, Giuliani and two extremist groups of violating a federal Reconstruction-era law known as the Ku Klux Klan Act.

value.title: Georgia state bar proceeding with inquiry into pro-Trump attorney Lin Wood
value.excerpt: The State Bar of Georgia is "proceeding with an inquiry" into attorney Lin Wood, one of the lawyers who unsuccessfully pushed a handful of suits to block Georgia's election results after alleging unfounded claims of fraud, the organization told CNN in a statement Tuesday.

value.title: Lincoln Project's Rick Wilson raised $64G for anti-Trump film that was never released
value.excerpt: Rick Wilson, co-founder of the anti-Trump Lincoln Project PAC, raised nearly $65,000 for an in-production film called "Everything Trump Touches Dies" that has yet to be released.

value.title: OP-ED: Pence was a potential victim on Jan. 6. That doesn't make him a hero
value.excerpt: When he issued a statement early on Jan. 6 indicating that he lacked the unilateral authority to determine which electoral votes should be counted, Vice President Mike Pence was stating the obvious. It was a "Profiles in Courage" moment only by the low standards of the Trump administration.

value.title: Comey email reveals FBI, DOJ made 'premeditated effort to dislodge' Trump from office: Gaetz
value.excerpt: The Justice Department and FBI engaged in a "premeditated effort to dislodge the duly elected president of the United States," Rep. Matt Gaetz, R-Fla., charged Monday on "Hannity."

value.title: GOP Sen. Richard Burr facing censure at home over vote to convict Trump
value.excerpt: The North Carolina GOP is set to vote on a censure on retiring Sen. Richard Burr in an emergency meeting Monday.

value.title: Progressives Push for Joe Biden's $1,400 Stimulus Checks on President's Day: '44 Days'
value.excerpt: Before taking office, Biden said that he wanted to act "boldly and urgently" to get the checks passed through Congress. But weeks have gone by since his inauguration and another stimulus bill has still not been passed.

value.title: Trump drives past jubilant supporters at impromptu rally in Florida
value.excerpt: Former President Trump marked President’s Day by waiving to a throng of supporters gathered near his south Florida residence.
